1 SECTION 16, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
2 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. Except for those cases in which the juvenile
3 court has no jurisdiction in accordance with IC 31-30-1-4, the court
4 shall, upon motion of the prosecuting attorney and after full
5 investigation and hearing, waive jurisdiction if it finds that:
6 (1) the child is charged with an act that, if committed by an adult,
7 would be:
8 (A) a Level 1 felony, Level 2 felony, Level 3 felony, or Level
9 4 felony, except a felony defined by IC 35-48-4;
10 (B) involuntary manslaughter as a Level 5 felony under
11 IC 35-42-1-4; or
12 (C) reckless homicide as a Level 5 felony under IC 35-42-1-5;
13 or
14 (D) unlawful carrying of a handgun as a felony under
15 IC 35-47-2-1.5;
16 (2) there is probable cause to believe that the child has committed
17 the act; and
18 (3) the child was at least sixteen (16) years of age when the act
19 charged was allegedly committed;
20 unless it would be in the best interests of the child and of the safety and
21 welfare of the community for the child to remain within the juvenile
22 justice system.
